<h2>Installation</h2>

<h3>Creating an Ember Project</h3>

<p>Before starting your first Ember Theater project, you'll need to ensure that you have Ember CLI installed. You can find an excellent guide <a href="https://guides.emberjs.com/v2.2.0/getting-started/" target="_blank">here</a>. You'll only have to go through this process once.</p>

<p>Once Ember CLI is installed, you can create as many projects as you like. To start a project, simply enter <code>ember new [project name]</code> in your terminal.</p>

<h3>Installing the Ember Theater addon</h3>

<p>Within your project folder, type <code>ember install ember-theater</code>. NPM will now start downloading Ember Theater. This can take a few minutes.</p>

